metadata.name: COMPUTERS #49
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from pixel array computations and classic noise algorithms.

COMPUTERS is a meditation on the aesthetics of computing in all of its forms. It recalls the types of computation required to build temples, write complex texts, weave detailed textiles, and program computer games. Pixels have always existed in some form or another, before and after the screen. Every iteration of COMPUTERS suggests that computation is both contemporary and ancient.

Press 'p' or click to pause the animation.
Press 's' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: Imi #53
metadata.description:
Recursive subdivision based on "returns", inspired by Imi Knoebel. (German painter and sculptor known for his contributions to and shaping of 20th century Minimalist abstract art.)

Click for new composition, doubleclick for fullscreen. Press s to save a printable SVG file.

metadata.name: Trillingen #20
metadata.description:
Trillingen is the next evolution of the Familiar Relations project. It is a visual representation of the knowledge, beauty, and pain that vibrates from one generation to the next. 

- Press [ r ] to change circle and outline colors
- Press [ s ] to save image to disk as a .png

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Sand Table #196
metadata.description:
Just like a sand jar that you made or played with as a child. A recreation of layered colored sand with star glitter at the "peaks." Rare versions will be all gold and super rare has rainbow shimmer glitter.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 20 color palettes
- 2 color distribution methods
- 4 sand distribution methods
- sand size variation
- noise variables to determine patterns and layers

Rare features
- color sand with gold stars
- all stars instead of sand grains
- all gold glitter with silver stars
- all rainbow glitter with silver stars (super rare)

metadata.name: Shizukana Mirror #185
metadata.description:
Shizukana Mirror (靜鏡)
It was a funny journey to discover and imitate how the nature works. It's not possible to make it as perfect as the nature does. The scene was inspired by what I encounter in a park of Kyoto couple years ago. 

5% of sales goes to a Taiwanese stray animal organization.

metadata.name: Skull #12
metadata.description: After an unknown silence, we experience a beautiful carnival. One day this carnival will end, another unknown silence will begin. Let the flowers bloom after us.

metadata.name: A Less Traveled Path #208
metadata.description:
"I shall be telling this with a sigh
Somewhere ages and ages hence:
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—
I took the one less traveled by,
And that has made all the difference."

- Robert Frost, The Road Not Taken



=========

Controls:
[1] set resolution to 1024x1024 (default)
[2] set resolution to 2048x2048 
[3] set resolution to 4096x4096
[0] set resolution to window size (might help on lower end computers)

[c] capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment
XALTED 2022

metadata.name: Schetsboek (reissue) #111
metadata.description:
This is my little tribute to fx (hash and fam).

During an important phone call, I was put on hold. Unconsciously, I began to scribble in my sketchbook. Research shows that scribbling helps focusing, but I dreamed away nonetheless until my pages were filled with scribbles, notes, shopping and a to-do list. 

Mint a uniquely generated page from my non-existent 100% coded sketchbook (except text typography). 

The page may contain many scribbles and drawings in pen, felt-tip pen, pencil, or less: often references to artists I admire, some in the form of loose scribbles, others in the form of riddles. Those drawings are drawn with code and vary. Unfortunately, I wasn’t able to incorporate tributes to all art and every artist I admire. The sketchbook would never finish. Thanks to rudxane I know that it’s ok to publish something unfinished ;-). 

One reference that appears in every token is to Sol Lewitt, an incredible source of inspiration. His artworks consist of instructions. Your sketch book pages contain instructions too. You will find the instructions for the artwork scribbled on your unique page by pressing i.

Curious how the work would look without the ‘distracting’ scribbles and coffee stains? Press ‘a’, ‘w’, or ‘g’. 

800 x 800 px

Press ‘s’ to save an image.

Made with p5js and the amazing p5.scribble.js library by Janneck Wullschleger.

Font used: Sacremento-Regular under the SIL Open Font License (OFL).

See license.md for the licenses of both.

Thank you all!

metadata.name: Hard Development #14
metadata.description:
From a techincal point of view, Hard Development is a sum of consistent part of the techniques that I have been experimenting so far. In this piece I come back to  explore the theme of environmental impact that we are having on the planet and on out own lives. No far and distant alternative world for us right now but only the need to respect the only one that we have limiting pollution and respecting nature.
- hit 's' to save
